    {
      "id": "2f5fd2b5f21a28fd08f2a42772a2fa3d669c953d",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2015-07-10 20:40:40.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\nSince the checkpatch.pl script can used from the git commit hooks for any patch (contrib/git-hooks/prepare-commit-msg), this will complain about non-LU tickets for patches on any other branch, so I don't think this can land as-is.\n\nIt would be OK to have this check conditional for patches under fs/lustre-release, or possibly better to do this check in gerrit-checkpatch.pl so that we don't diverge checkpatch.pl too much from the upstream kernel version.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "912ace5bc9379087b0514ebed37e8cca7b0bb456",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 177,
        "name": "John Hammond",
        "email": "jhammond@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jhammond"
      },
      "date": "2015-07-10 20:51:12.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Since the checkpatch.pl script can used from the git commit hooks for any patch (contrib/git-hooks/prepare-commit-msg), this will complain about non-LU tickets for patches on any other branch, so I don't think this can land as-is.\n\nSince prepare-commit-msg uses 'git diff' and this checks the output of 'git format-patch' this will not be an issue.\n\n> It would be OK to have this check conditional for patches under fs/lustre-release, or possibly better to do this check in gerrit-checkpatch.pl so that we don't diverge checkpatch.pl too much from the upstream kernel version.\n\nThis change is for fs/lustre-release.\n\ngerrit_checkpatch.pl runs patches through checkpatch.pl and posts the results to gerrit. It is not the palce for this.\n\nOur checkpatch.pl is already pretty far from what's in upstream.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
